title: US moves to list giraffes under Endangered Species Act for first time
description: Climate crisis, habitat loss and poaching have reduced its numbers – but will Trump put the kibosh on protections?They are the tallest animal to roam the Earth and have become an icon of children’s books, toys and awed wildlife documentaries. But giraffes are in decline, which has prompted the US government to list them as endangered for the first time.Giraffes will be listed under the US Endangered Species Act, the US Fish and Wildlife Service has proposed in a move that will cover five subspecies of the animal. The agency hopes the listing will crack down on the poaching of giraffes, as the US is a leading destination of rugs, pillowcases, boots, furniture and even Bible covers made from giraffe body parts. title: Malian singer Rokia Traoré to be extradited from Italy to Belgium
description: Italy’s highest court rejects musician’s appeal after she was arrested in Rome in June over child custody disputeMalian musician Rokia Traoré, who was arrested in Rome last June over an international child custody dispute, will be handed over to Belgium in the coming days after Italy’s highest court rejected her appeal, her lawyer said on Wednesday.Traoré, 50, a former goodwill ambassador for the United Nations’ refugee agency UNHCR, was arrested on 20 June at Rome’s Fiumicino airport under a European arrest warrant. title: Donald Trump taps loyalist Pam Bondi for US attorney general after Matt Gaetz withdraws
description: Pam Bondi has been named as US Attorney General by Donald Trump, succeeding Matt Gaetz, who withdrew amid a federal investigation. Bondi, a staunch Trump ally, previously defended him in his first impeachment trial and supported him during his recent hush money trial. Trump praised Bondi's commitment and outlined his vision for the Department of Justice to prioritise crime fighting and national security.
author: TOI World Desk
